<!--Below is copied from glossary-->


<p>The <attr>extrapolateBackward</attr> and <attr>extrapolateForward</attr> of the <tag>curve</tag> components will add quadratic extrapolations onto cubic splines.  The extrapolation is based on the curvature of the adjacent spline segment.  The extrapolated parabola will open either vertically or horizontally.</p>

<p>Extrapolate backward: <booleanInput name="extBack" /></p>
<p>Extrapolate foward: <booleanInput name="extFor" /></p>

<graph>
  <curve through='(-3,-5) (-1, 4) (2,-3) (5,3)' extrapolateBackward="$extBack" extrapolateForward="$extFor">
  <bezierControls>
    (-2,-3) (-2,0) (-2,0) (-0.3,-2)
  </bezierControls>
  </curve>
</graph>












